data.description: Dating back to the 1840's, the Mayflower Farm in historic Elizabeth Township can be yours to call home. This Greek Revival/Federalist style home is impressive with spacious rooms and luxurious design elements.  Modern updates include a 70 year steel roof- 2021, new flat roofing 2021, new skylights, a fully modernized kitchen with quartzite counters and AGA Cooker stove, and a new heat pump to serve the north side of the home with heat and AC. The solarium features floor to ceiling windows and a heated terrazzo tile floor. On the second floor, you’ll find an expansive executive suite of rooms that includes the primary bedroom, two dressing rooms, a full bath, an executive study, and a private terrace overlooking the grounds. The property was once home to a riding club. The tree lined trails are still accessible. One of the three garage bays has flooring specifically designed to accommodate horses.  Other highlights of the home include a spacious and inviting tavern room, a butler pantry, a wine cellar, a formal dining room, and numerous seating areas. When the awning is in place, a 24 x 36 space is created that is ideal for outside entertaining. Per Eliz. Twp, this property may be used as in Inn or Bed & Breakfast so long as the owner is a resident.  There are many ways to create private spaces adjacent to full baths in this property. The elevator allows for ADA access and the huge gourmet kitchen can be utilized to feed a large gathering.
